<br><br><IMG height=110 src="/images/ces_photos/airport_01.jpg" width=150 align=right>The Clark County Department of Aviation is rolling up its sleeves to alleviate baggage claim headaches at the Las Vegas McCarran International Airport. Work began&nbsp;last month on the $12 million construction project, which includes plans to increase the capacity of eight baggage carousels, improve the foot traffic flow and install new signs to make it easier to find bags. 

